---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../config';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About Mossroom"
  description="Mossroom is the honest terrarium resource — run by people who are figuring this out, alongside you."
>
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16">
    <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-moss-900 mb-6">
      About Mossroom
    </h1>

    <div class="prose-moss">
      <p class="text-xl text-soil-700 leading-relaxed">
        Mossroom exists because terrarium advice on the internet is a mess.
      </p>

      <p>
        If you've ever tried to build one, you know. Reddit threads go in circles.
        YouTube tutorials contradict each other. Blog posts from 2011 say things
        that may or may not still be true. Nobody actually explains <em>why</em> —
        they just tell you what to do.
      </p>

      <p>
        We're not master horticulturists. We're people who got tired of being
        confused by our own hobby. So we built the resource we wished existed:
        one place, clear answers, honest about what we don't know.
      </p>

      <h2>What you'll find here</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Care guides that explain the reasoning, not just the steps</li>
        <li>Plant profiles for species that actually work in jars</li>
        <li>Where to source moss, driftwood, and the hard-to-find stuff</li>
        <li>Diagnosis help when something's dying and you don't know why</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>What you won't find</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Fake expertise.</strong> If we don't know, we say so.</li>
        <li>Sponsored posts disguised as guides</li>
        <li>AI-written content that sounds helpful but isn't</li>
        <li>Gatekeeping about who counts as a "real" hobbyist</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Who this is for</h2>
      <p>
        Anyone who's ever killed a terrarium and wants to figure out why.
        Beginners looking for a clear starting point. People who like tiny worlds
        and want company while they figure it out.
      </p>

      <p>
        You don't need a green thumb. You need clear information and a community
        that helps when things go sideways. That's what we're building.
      </p>

      <h2>Get involved</h2>
      <p>
        Have a build you're proud of? A question nobody's answered? A plant that
        won't stop dying? Drop into the Discord — it's the fastest way to get help
        and the easiest way to help the next person.
      </p>

      <p>
        Want a weekly terrarium tip in your inbox?
        <a href="#newsletter">Subscribe to the newsletter</a> — one small thing,
        every Friday.
      </p>

      <p>
        Want to write for us, share a build, or report something that needs fixing?
        Email <a href={`mailto:${SITE.email}`}>{SITE.email}</a>.
      </p>

      <hr class="my-12 border-moss-200" />

      <p class="text-soil-600 italic">
        Mossroom is built by humans who are still figuring it out, alongside you.
        That's the whole point.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
